{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"9aa447fb-2337-4e67-afd2-46534393846d","content":"Here's the summary:\n\n| Property | .NET 9 | .NET 10 |\n|---|---|---|\n| `EnableMSTestRunner` | Required ✅ | Required ✅ |\n| `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` | Required (opt-in) ✅ | **Not needed** ❌ |\n\n**What changed in .NET 10:** `dotnet test` natively speaks the Microsoft Testing Platform protocol, so the bridge property (`TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport`) that opted into MTP in .NET 9 is now the default behavior. Your `EnableMSTestRunner` property is still needed — it tells MSTest to build as an executable test host. Everything else just works with `dotnet test`.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"3922dfc2-76b6-4046-98fb-d220e549203e","outputTokens":180,"requestId":"BD06:2EBD81:1CB0E85:206A927:6A07C5C7"},"id":"d190f50e-798f-4c35-b8e0-ffedb099e68f","timestamp":"2026-05-16T01:18:04.594Z","parentId":"5599c485-e30c-4cd3-b46e-eda9b2a48d73"}
